title: (x) ViCrew logo - Deftones {Chesh}
content:
I'm redesigning a logo for ViCrew, a Dragonboating team from U of T, They have this wordmark on their webpage, I want to use something with a similar feel to it.   
   
 ![Vicrew Wordmark](http://web.archive.org/web/20050528000512im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/26626.jpg)   
   
Does anyone recognize this particular typeface?
author: myoung

comments.content: Looks like [Deftones](http://web.archive.org/web/20050528000512/http:/www.dafont.com/en/search.php?q=deftones&nb_ppp_old=10&page=1&texte=Vilcrew&nb_ppp=10) with a modified lower-case l.

I don't know what I was thinking just there -- that's a capital C. Now it's just Deftones, [completely unmodified](http://web.archive.org/web/20050528000512/http:/www.dafont.com/en/search.php?q=deftones&nb_ppp_old=10&page=1&texte=ViCrew&nb_ppp=10&Envoyer=%A0OK%A0). Don't mind me, I'm on a vacation day.
Thanks, I really suspected it was a free font.
